class Solution {
    public int rob(int[] nums) {
        if (nums.length == 1){
            return nums[0];
        }
        if (nums.length == 2){
            return Math.max(nums[0], nums[1]);
        }
        int [] dp = new int[nums.length];
        dp[0] = nums[0];
        dp[1] = Math.max(nums[0], nums[1]);
        for (int i = 2; i < nums.length; i++){
            dp[i] = Math.max(dp[i - 2] + nums[i], dp[i - 1]);
        }
        return dp[nums.length - 1];
    }
}

/*
Notes:

(Using “Dynamic Programming” + “Rolling Array”)

Value functions of Q198: 
dp [ i ] = max(dp[ i – 2 ] + i , dp[ i - 1])

Explanation: 
If we choose the current the element, then the current maximum is the sum of current element and 2 position left element.
If we don’t choose the current the element, then the current maximum is the maximum of 1 position left element of current element.

*”Boundary condition”: 
1. We set the first element of dp array exclusively.
2. We set the second element of dp array exclusively.
3. We start from third element to iterate.

*/
